          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Israel raids West Bank</h2> 
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-jan-24-1.png" alt="Israel raids West Bank" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>Summary: Israel launched an operation into the West Bank only a few days after the ceasefire-hostage deal was realized.</strong></p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Israeli forces launched a <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-01-2025-h1-1-large-scale-operation" target="_blank">large-scale operation</a> in Jenin, West Bank, this week involving airstrikes, road demolitions, and mass arrests. They are targeting what they described as “terror infrastructure.” At least 10 Palestinians were killed, over 40 were injured, and access to medical aid was restricted as ambulances were blocked. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">PM Benjamin Netanyahu faces pressure from his far-right allies following the truce. Meanwhile, masked groups <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-01-2025-linked-to-jewish-settlers" target="_blank">linked to Jewish settlers</a> attacked Palestinian villages, causing violence and destruction. The situation in the West Bank raises concerns that the ceasefire, which is already very fragile, could collapse.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Donald Trump has also <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-01-2025-h1-2-reversed-sanctions" target="_blank">reversed sanctions</a> against 30 groups of West Bank settlers the Biden administration previously implemented. He also said he was “not confident” that the ceasefire would hold and commented, “It's not our war, it's their war.” With Netanyahu's coalition encountering internal strife, it could cause calls for a stricter stance against Palestinians.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
