          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Zelenskyy demands peacekeepers</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-jan-24-2.png" alt="Zelenskyy demands peacekeepers" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>Summary: Zelenskyy says that allied troops would be needed to negotiate a peace deal with Russia and stresses the need for Europe to defend the continent.</strong></p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">President Volodymyr Zelenskyy said that "at least 200,000" allied troops would be necessary to enforce any peace deal in Ukraine during his address at the World Economic Forum in Davos (<a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-01-2025-h2-3-full-speech" target="_blank">full speech</a>). He urged European leaders to take proactive steps to defend their continent from Russian aggression and the return of Donald Trump.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Zelenskyy stressed the need for Europe to unite, adding, “Europe needs to learn how to take care of itself fully, so the world cannot afford to ignore it.” Ukrainians assert that if Putin wins the war in Ukraine, he will move on to attack other nations. Zelensky has also called into question the reliability of the US and its role in NATO.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">This comes amid Trump's demands that Russia and Ukraine work on a peace plan to end the war. Zelensky’s input is another testament to Europe’s increasing anxiety about Ukraine's future and security during this Trump administration. NATO Secretary General Mark Rutte stated at Davos that Trump is right about <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-01-2025-h2-4-defense-spending" target="_blank">defense spending</a>, and Europe needs to improve its defense to mitigate any problems.</p>
        </mj-text>
