          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Putin-Xi phone call</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>Summary: The Russian and Chinese presidents had a long phone call immediately following the inauguration to discuss their concerns.</strong></p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">
          Chinese President Xi Jinping and Russian President Vladimir Putin had a 90-minute video call just hours after Donald Trump's inauguration. During the call, they discussed building ties with Trump through his unpredictable presidency. Trump has threatened to impose tariffs on China and warned Russia about potential repercussions if it failed to resolve the conflict in Ukraine (<a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-01-2025-h3-5-kremlin-press-release" target="_blank">Kremlin press release</a>).
</p>
<p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">
          The two countries declared a <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-01-2025-h3-6-no-limiit-partnership" target="_blank">"no-limits partnership”</a> in 2022. Putin referred to Xi as a dear friend and supported strengthening bilateral ties despite external pressures. Xi Jinping called for deeper cooperation and mutual support between China and Russia. He added that they coordinate their actions across various multilateral institutions, including the United Nations and its Security Council, the SCO, the G20, and APEC. 
</p>
<p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">
          Vladimir Putin stressed that any peace agreement regarding Ukraine must consider Russia’s interests. The two leaders also discussed various global issues, including the Middle East and Taiwan, while reaffirming their commitment to improving trade and military cooperation. "Xi will play a decisive role in the early end of the war in Ukraine that Trump has promised,” said Graham Allison, Douglas Dillon Professor of Government at Harvard University. 
</p>
        </mj-text>
