          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">
          <strong>🇬🇧 Russian spy ship entered UK waters again. Royal Navy has deployed advanced AI systems and Maritime patrol.</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">UK’s Royal Navy has stepped up efforts to safeguard critical undersea infrastructure following the return of the Russian spy vessel, Yantar, to its waters. Yantar was seen in the channel last November; the ship passed through the English Channel this week while being monitored by HMS Somerset. The UK is leading in countering the growing Russian threat to offshore infrastructure in European seas (<a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-01-2025-br2-9-royal-navy-news" target="_blank">Royal Navy news</a>).</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Defence Secretary John Healey announced that Britain would enhance surveillance measures, including deploying the advanced Nordic Warden AI system and increasing NATO cooperation with maritime patrols. Healey said, “We know what you are doing, and we will not shy away from robust action to protect Britain.” These actions come amid fears of potential Russian sabotage, particularly the damage to the Estlink2 cable last December. The Kremlin has not yet provided any comment.</p>
        </mj-text>
