          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">What is the Eurasian Economic Union?</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-jan-24-3.png" alt="What is the Eurasian Economic Union?" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-01-2025-f1-10-eurasian-economic-union" target="_blank">Eurasian Economic Union</a> (EAEU), established on January 1, 2015, is a regional economic organization that promotes economic integration among its five member states: <strong>Armenia, Belarus, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, and Russia</strong>. The EAEU facilitates the free movement of goods, services, capital, and labor within a common market similar to the European Union.</p>
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The EAEU was established based on the Customs Union and the Common Economic Space, which have unified trade policies and put efforts to harmonize regulations in energy, agriculture, and transportation. Some people view the EAEU as Russia's response to the EU. However, there are significant <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-01-2025-f1-11-difference-between-the-two-entities" target="_blank">differences between the two entities</a>.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Russia dominates the EAEU and has only five member states, while the EU has 27 members, with no single dominant country. Additionally, the EAEU does not have a common currency and does not enforce uniform policies in areas like foreign relations or defense. In contrast, the EU is characterized by more significant political and economic integration, whereas the EAEU primarily focuses on economic cooperation without extensive political integration.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
